  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Relay box removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The relay box is an integral part of the engine compartment wire harness and cannot be replaced by itself. Therefore, if the relay box is defective, replace the engine compartment wire harness."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. 12V battery terminal disconnected",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000910",
          "label": "12V battery terminal disconnected",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Relay box removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "924_3.0_jpn_11365525_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the upper cover (B) from the relay box (A). Disconnect the cable (C). Remove the relay box from the bracket (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    }
  ],
